# Phase 2 / Slice 2 — Assessment + AssessmentScore + score-entry API

Plan-first against phase-2.md slice 2, then cp1 build. Plan approved with
three explicit calls on the flagged items.

## Settled implementation decisions (slice 2)

- **Q1 — materialization timing:** (a) SAME tx as the score write. The UI
  reads totalScore + letterGrade from the POST/PATCH response, so the
  summary must be materialized before the response returns; a separate tx
  or BullMQ would let score and summary diverge. Reuses the cp1
  mutate→re-read→recompute→upsert→return shape inside one withTenant tx.
- **Q2 — bulk tx shape:** (a) ATOMIC all-or-nothing. A gradebook column
  save is one interactive edit, not a 10k-row import (the opposite of the
  Phase-1 CSV per-row choice). Pre-validate every row up front, then one
  tx writes all rows + re-materializes one Assessment per distinct student.
- **Q3 — teacher-scope integration:** (b) BULK PRE-CHECK. One getTeacherScope
  call + one enrollment.findMany for all batch students; validate every row
  in memory (subject ∈ subjectsByArm[student's enrollment arm this term])
  before any write. The same enrollment fetch supplies Assessment.classArmId
  (double duty). No N+1. (c RLS-enforced scope rejected by spec.)
- **Q4 — cp split:** Split 1 (service-spec-first). cp1 = models + migration
  + RLS + RLS spec + DTOs + PURE compute/validate functions with unit tests
  written FIRST. cp2 = single-score endpoint + materialization + scope +
  integration spec. cp3 = bulk + bulk-scope + sign-off + freeze guard +
  integration spec.
- **Q5 — componentId validation:** (a) RLS-scoped fetch as the primary guard
  (cross-tenant id → null → ValidationError) + explicit belt-and-braces
  assert component.schoolId === authCtx.schoolId. Live component.weight is
  the strict ceiling; never trust a client-supplied max.
- **Q6 — sign-off + re-edit:** confirmed. A score POST/PATCH on a signed-off
  Assessment clears subjectSignedOffAt/By in the same tx; the implicit
  unlock is metadata ({ clearedSignOff: true }) on the score-change audit
  row, not a second action. Slice 6 owns the real workflow gate.

## Three flagged calls (user decisions)

- **Flag #1 (admin scope): CONFIRMED** role gate ["owner","admin","teacher"],
  admins UNSCOPED. Real ops (teacher quits mid-term, sick teacher,
  substitute) need admin score entry; enteredBy captures the override in
  audit. Phase-1 roster precedent (admins unscoped, teachers scoped).
- **Flag #2 (freeze guard): INCLUDE NOW in cp3**, touching slice-1 code.
  REFINEMENT: the conservative invariant — ANY assessment_scores row for the
  SCHOOL exists → scheme frozen until an audited reset. Do NOT scope to
  "active term only" (the fuzzy active-term concept invites the retroactive-
  recompute footgun: finish Term 1 → edit scheme → Term 1 cards recompute
  against the new scheme). Simpler invariant prevents that categorically.
  Error: "This scheme is frozen because scores have been entered. To change
  the scheme, an admin must reset scores first (audited)." (Reset path is
  deferred per phase-2.md — link the deferred entry if practical.) Worth one
  line in cp3's commit message.
- **Flag #3 (no-enrollment): CONFIRMED** reject with ValidationError
  ("Student is not enrolled this term"). Atomic bulk → one unenrolled
  student rejects the whole batch.

