# Phase 2 / Slice 3 — Gradebook grid UI

Slice 2 closed (cp1 models/pure-fns + cp2 single-score + cp3 bulk/sign-off/
freeze, all on main). Slice 3 is the first major Phase-2 UI: the form-class
discipline at GRID scale. Plan-first against phase-2.md slice 3; plan approved
with all flagged decisions going to my leans.

## The one backend touch (Flag #0)
Teachers can't resolve a termId: term.read is admin-gated and the teacher role
lacks it, but the feed/bulk/sign-off endpoints all REQUIRE termId. Fix:
extend GET /teacher-scope/me with `currentTerm: { id, name, sequence } | null`
resolved from Term.isCurrent inside the existing withTenant. Single source of
teacher context, no new permission/route. The gradebook is CURRENT-TERM only
in slice 3 (multi-term selection deferred); the picker is effectively
arm → subject. Lands in cp1.

## Settled decisions
- **Q1 save model:** explicit Save button only (cp3's bulk is atomic — auto-
  save makes that murky). Payload = DIRTY cells only (RHF dirtyFields).
  beforeunload guard when dirty cells exist (crash-recovery mitigation).
- **Q2 position column:** show with "—" placeholder, bound to
  assessment.subjectPosition (the gradebook-relevant per-subject rank;
  classPosition is the report-card overall position). Populated by slice 4.
- **Q3 per-cell errors:** per-cell primary (parse bulk path ['rows', i,
  'score'] → red border + chip on the offending cell) + a thin summary banner
  for the tall-grid scroll case. Most range errors surface pre-submit via the
  client per-cell 0..weight refine; server path-bound issues are the backstop
  (freeze, server-side weight change).
- **Q4 sign-off gating:** disabled until (every cell filled AND no unsaved
  dirty cells) with an adaptive explainer ("Save your changes first" vs "Fill
  in all scores to sign off"). After success → locked (inputs disabled +
  "Signed off ✓" badge) + "Re-open to edit" (client-side re-enable); saving a
  changed score clears sign-off server-side (cp3 implicit unlock).
- **Q5 cp split:** Split 1 (data-first). cp1 = currentTerm extension +
  assessment-api wrappers + /teacher/gradebook picker + grid rendering
  read-only (Total/Grade/Position read-only) with editable score cells +
  per-cell client validation, NO save + loading/empty/scope-404 states +
  sidebar Gradebook entry + teacher-scope spec extension. cp2 = Save (bulk) +
  per-cell error binding + summary banner + beforeunload guard + Sign-off
  column (gating + lock + Re-open) + manual browser pass.
- **Q6 number-cell shape:** FormValues = { rows: [{ studentId, scores:
  Record<componentId, string> }] } via useFieldArray + dotted registration
  rows.${i}.scores.${componentId}. Cells hold STRING (empty = unentered),
  coerced to int at save. makeGradebookSchema(components) factory parametrizes
  the discipline by the loaded scheme (superRefine validates each cell vs its
  component.weight, binds issues to ['rows', i, 'scores', componentId]). Zero
  `as never`; FormValues schema separate from the bulk API body schema.

## Acceptance #7 ("no total/grade computed in the browser")
Total/Grade/Position are READ-ONLY cells bound to feed[i].assessment.* — never
summed client-side. After save, pessimistic re-render: trust the bulk
response's refreshed feed. The only client computation is per-cell range
validation (input validation, not grading).

